Lemon Buttermilk Cornmeal Pound Cake
  --@wickdconfections

Yield: 1 bundt or tube cake (12–16 slices)

Cake
1 c (227 g) unsalted butter, softened
2 c (400 g) sugar 
4 large eggs, room temp
1 tbsp lemon zest
1 tsp (5 ml) vanilla extract
1 1/2 c (180 g) ap flour
1/2 c (80 g) fine cornmeal
1/2 tsp (2 g) baking powder
1/2 tsp (2 g) baking soda
1 tsp (6 g) salt
1 c (240 ml) buttermilk
2 tbsp (30 ml) lemon juice

Heat oven to 325F / 163C. Grease and flour a bundt or tube pan. Cream butter and sugar 3–5 min until light and fluffy. Beat in eggs one at a time. Add lemon zest and vanilla. Whisk flour, cornmeal, baking powder, baking soda, and salt. Mix buttermilk and lemon juice together. Alternate adding dry ingredients and buttermilk mixture, beginning and ending with dry. Mix just until combined. Bake 65–75 minutes until a toothpick comes out clean. Cool 15 minutes, then turn out and cool completely.

Lemon Glaze
1 1/2 c (180 g) powdered sugar
2–3 tbsp (30–45 ml) lemon juice
1 tbsp (14 g) melted butter
pinch salt

Whisk glaze ingredients until pourable. Drizzle over cooled cake. Let glaze set, slice, and serve




Let glaze set, slice, and serve 
